    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-23T01:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-23T01:30:00-05:00" n="340"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">689.90D/5–2351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Pakistan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Karachi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-23T12:00:00+05:30"
                            >May 23, 1951—noon.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1109. I conveyed to <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> yesterday afternoon
                    Dept’s position re para 1 Ikramullah ltr, May 15, <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 755, May 18. Zafrulla said it was mot in his opinion
                    intention <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> to project US as arbiter of
                    agreement but only to satisfy itself as to Dept attitude shld <gloss
                        target="#t_GOA1">GOA</gloss> persist in <pb facs="0511" n="1975"
                        xml:id="pg_1975"/> its proPushtoonistan propaganda. I reiterated sense of
                    first sentence ref <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> and Zafrulla said
                    he wld clarify matter with <gloss target="#t_PM1">PM</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Be memo May 15 Zafrulla said it was not his understanding that <gloss
                        target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> intended to preclude <gloss target="#t_Pak1"
                        >Pak</gloss> Amb at Kabul from discussing matters of common concern and that
                    he wld also clarify this understanding with <gloss target="#t_PM1"
                    >PM</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Zafrulla then expressed hope that we wld now come to final agreement on text of
                        <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> acceptance and suggested that that shld
                    be the case assuming <gloss target="#t_PM1">PM</gloss> confirms his (Zafrulla’s)
                    understanding of <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> intent as expressed
                    above.</p>
                <p>I recommend to Dept that if <gloss target="#t_PM1">PM</gloss> approves Zafrulla’s
                    statement of intent and understanding on both points raised ref <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> that we tell <gloss target="#t_GOP1"
                        >GOP</gloss> that their May 15 memo will be transmitted to <gloss
                        target="#t_GOA1">GOA</gloss> as constituting <gloss target="#t_Pak1"
                        >Pak</gloss> acceptance our <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi>.</p>
                <p>Dept pass London; sent Dept 1109, rptd info Kabul 60, London 78.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
